From: Evgenii Lepikhin <johnlepikhin@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Honour ZE_DRIVER_PATH env var and dlopen UMDs by absolute path

Upstream's `getLibrarySearchPaths()` only consults `LD_LIBRARY_PATH`
and a list of well-known FHS directories (`/lib`, `/usr/lib`,
`/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu`, ...) when looking for `libze_intel_*.so.1`.
On Guix System none of those directories exist; the loader returns
an empty driver list and consumers (OpenVINO, oneAPI tooling) see no
NPU/GPU at all.

Two changes, both in `source/loader/linux/driver_discovery_lin.cpp`:

1. Read a parallel `ZE_DRIVER_PATH` env var with the same
   colon-separated semantics as `LD_LIBRARY_PATH`.  The Guix
   `level-zero` package declares a `native-search-paths` for that
   variable pointing at `lib/`, so any package in the profile that
   ships a Level Zero UMD (`intel-compute-runtime`,
   `intel-npu-driver`, ...) contributes its store path automatically.
   This solves the file-existence check.

2. Have `discoverEnabledDrivers()` carry the absolute path at which
   the UMD was found back to the loader instead of the bare SONAME.
   Upstream then passes that string straight to `LOAD_DRIVER_LIBRARY`
   (a dlopen wrapper) in `source/loader/ze_loader.cpp`, so the
   dynamic linker sees an absolute path and loads the file directly
   -- bypassing the `DT_RUNPATH` of `libze_loader.so` (which would
   otherwise have to include every UMD's store path).  Without this
   second change the stat-check finds the file but the subsequent
   dlopen still goes through the linker's standard search and fails
   because `DT_RUNPATH` doesn't list the UMD packages.

Together: tools running under Guix don't need `LD_LIBRARY_PATH` (it
would pollute every dlopen, not just the loader's) and the UMD
packages don't have to be in `level-zero`'s `inputs` (which would
make `intel-compute-runtime` / `intel-npu-driver` indirectly load via
their build-time dependencies on `level-zero` -- a cycle).
---
--- a/source/loader/linux/driver_discovery_lin.cpp	2026-05-25 15:05:32.598502335 +0300
+++ b/source/loader/linux/driver_discovery_lin.cpp	2026-05-25 15:06:36.125801303 +0300
@@ -40,6 +40,14 @@
 // Helper to get all library search paths from LD_LIBRARY_PATH, standard locations, and /etc/ld.so.conf
 static std::vector<std::string> getLibrarySearchPaths() {
   std::vector<std::string> paths;
+  // ZE_DRIVER_PATH: Guix-friendly alternative to LD_LIBRARY_PATH for
+  // UMD discovery.  Declared as a `native-search-paths` in Guix's
+  // `level-zero` package; the profile fans out store paths there.
+  const char* zeDriverPath = getenv("ZE_DRIVER_PATH");
+  if (zeDriverPath) {
+    auto split = splitPaths(zeDriverPath);
+    paths.insert(paths.end(), split.begin(), split.end());
+  }
   // LD_LIBRARY_PATH
   const char* ldLibPath = getenv("LD_LIBRARY_PATH");
   if (ldLibPath) {
@@ -108,16 +116,21 @@
   return paths;
 }
 
-// Main function: search for a library file in all known library paths
-static bool libraryExistsInSearchPaths(const std::string& filename) {
+// Search for `filename` in all known library paths and return the
+// absolute path at which it was found (or empty if absent).  The
+// caller hands this absolute path straight to LOAD_DRIVER_LIBRARY so
+// dlopen bypasses DT_RUNPATH of libze_loader.so entirely -- crucial
+// on Guix where the loader's RUNPATH does not list the UMD packages
+// and we can't (and shouldn't) modify LD_LIBRARY_PATH.
+static std::string locateLibrary(const std::string& filename) {
   auto paths = getLibrarySearchPaths();
   for (const auto& dir : paths) {
     std::string fullPath = dir + "/" + filename;
     if (fileExistsReadable(fullPath)) {
-      return true;
+      return fullPath;
     }
   }
-  return false;
+  return std::string();
 }
 
 namespace loader {
@@ -137,11 +150,12 @@
   altDrivers = getenv("ZE_ENABLE_ALT_DRIVERS");
   if (altDrivers == nullptr) {
     // Standard drivers - not custom
-    for (auto path : knownDriverNames) {
-      if (libraryExistsInSearchPaths(path)) {
+    for (auto soname : knownDriverNames) {
+      const std::string fullPath = locateLibrary(soname);
+      if (!fullPath.empty()) {
         // Extract the base library name for robust driver type detection
-        // path is like "libze_intel_gpu.so.1"
-        std::string libName = path;
+        // soname is like "libze_intel_gpu.so.1"
+        std::string libName = soname;
 
         // Remove "lib" prefix if present
         if (libName.compare(0, 3, "lib") == 0) {
@@ -165,7 +179,7 @@
           driverType = ZEL_DRIVER_TYPE_NPU;
         }
 
-        enabledDrivers.emplace_back(path, false, driverType);
+        enabledDrivers.emplace_back(fullPath, false, driverType);
       }
     }
   } else {
